stribution": "Endemic to the Philippines. MINDANAO: Sultan Kudarat.", "notes": "Low elevation primary dipterocarp forest.", "conservation_status": "Critically Endangered (IUCN 3.1).", "dao_category": "", "other_fields": {}, "gallery_url": "", "thumbs": [], "full": []}, {"u": 175, "scientific_name": "Hydnocarpus heterophyllus", "taxon_name": "Hydnocarpus heterophyllus", "category": "", "status": "Native.", "citation": "Blume , Rumphia 4 (1849) 22, as 'heterophylla' ; Sleumer, Fl. Males. ser. 1, 5 (1954) 20. ssp. philippinensis Sleumer, Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 69 (1938) 20; Fl. Males. ser. 1, 5 (1954) 20. = Cyclostemon iwahigensis Elmer, LPB 4 (1911) 1278. ≠ Taraktogenos heterophylla auct. non (Blume) Slooten; Merr., EPFP 3 (1923) 108. Distribution: Borneo, Philippines, Sulawesi. BUSUANGA, DINAGAT, LEYTE, LUZON: Camarines, Sorsogon, MASBATE, MINDORO, NEGROS, PALAWAN, PANAY, TABLAS, TICAO. Notes: Low elevation forests. Native.", "distribution": "Borneo, Java, Philippines, Sulawesi, Sumatra. BUSUANGA, DINAGAT, LEYTE, LUZON: Camarines, Sorsogon, MASBATE, MINDORO, NEGROS, PALAWAN, PANAY, SAMAR, TABLAS, TICAO.", "notes": "150-900m.", "conservation_status": "Least Concern (IUCN 3.1).", "dao_category": "", "other_fields": {}, "gallery_url": "", "thumbs": [], "full": []}, {"u": 176, "scientific_name": "Hydnocarpus polypetalus", "taxon_name": "Hydnocarpus polypetalus", "category": "", "status": "Native.", "citation": "(Slooten) Sleumer , Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 69 (1938) 62, as 'polypetala' ; Fl. Males. ser. 1, 5 (1954) 31; Soejarto et al., Prelim. Checklist Fl. Pl. Palawan (1995); ≡ Taraktogenos polypetalum Slooten , Bijdr. Combret. Flacourt. Ned.-Ind. (1919) 74.", "distribution": "Borneo, Philippines, Sumatra. PALAWAN.", "notes": "Lowland to medium elevation primary forest. 10-600m.", "conservation_status": "Least Concern (IUCN 3.1).", "dao_category": "", "other_fields": {}, "gallery_url": "", "thumbs": [], "full": []}, {"u": 177, "scientific_name": "Hydnocarpus subfalcatus", "taxon_name": "Hydnocarpus subfalcatus", "category": "", "status": "Native.", "citation": "Merr. , PJS 4c (1909) 297, as 'subfalcata' ; Merrill, EPFP 3 (1923) 107; Sleumer, Fl. Males. ser. 1, 5 (1954) 22. = Hydnocarpus ovoideus Elmer , LPB 4 (1912) 1514, as 'ovoidea'; Type: Elmer 12410, Sibuyan: Magallanes, Mt Giting-giting, May-1910. = Hydnocarpus quadrasii Elmer , LPB 4 (1912) 1515 ; Merrill, EPFP 3 (1923) 107; Type: Elmer 12085, Sibuyan: Magallanes, Mt Giting-giting, Mar-1910.", "distribution": "Borneo, Philippines, Sumatra. LUZON: Aurora, Cagayan, Isabela, Pangasinan, Quezon, Zambales, MINDANAO: Misamis Occidental, Surigao, SAMAR, SIBUYAN.", "notes": "Low elevation thickets and forests, on non-inundated level ground. 15-25m.", "conservation_status": "Least Concern (IUCN 3.1).", "dao_category": "", "other_fields": {}, "gallery_url": "", "thumbs": [], "full": []}, {"u": 178, "scientific_name": "Hydnocarpus sumatranus", "taxon_name": "Hydnocarpus sumatranus", "category": "", "status": "Native.", "citation": "(Miq.) Koord. , Syst. Verz. (Koord.-Schum.) 1 (1911) 2, as 'sumatrana' ; Sleumer, Fl. Males. ser. 1, 5 (1954) 27; ≡ Bergsmia sumatrana Miq. , Fl. Ned. Ind., Eerste Bijv. (1861) 389. = Hydnocarpus hutchinsonii Merr. , PJS 17 (1920) 291 ; Merrill, EPFP 3 (1923) 107. var. sumatranus. Distribution: Borneo, Java, Philippines, Sulawesi, Sumatra. BASILAN, MINDANAO: Zamboanga del Norte (photos), TAWI-TAWI. Notes: Rainforests, never in inundated areas, on sandy or clayey soil and hilly or steep ground. 30-200m. Native. var. pentagynus (Slooten) Sleumer, Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 69 (1938) 52, as 'pentagyna'; Fl. Males. ser. 1, 5 (1954) 28; ≡ Hydnocarpus pentagynus Slooten, Bijdr. Combret. Flacourt. Ned.-Ind. (1919) 64. = Hydnocarpus palawanensis Merr. & Quisumb., PJS 82 (1953) 330. Distribution: ?Borneo, ?Philippines, Sumatra. ?PALAWAN. Notes: Known with certainty only from a single collection from Sumatra. Very similar but not quite identical specimen have been found in Palawan in Puerto Princesa (PNH 192 Edano). This was described as Hydnocarpus palawanensis Merr. & Quisumb. Similar materials have also been found in Borneo (Sarawak and Mt Kinabalu). 200m.", "distribution": "Borneo, Java, Philippines, Sulawesi, Sumatra. BASILAN, LUZON: Laguna, MINDANAO: Zamboanga, Zamboanga Sibugay, Zamboanga del Norte (photos), MINDORO, ?PALAWAN, TAWI-TAWI.", "notes": "30-200m.", "conservation_status": "Least Concern (IUCN 3.1).", "dao_category": "", "other_fields": {}, "gallery_url": "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/bhbase/cubic_gallery_public.pl?start_at=0&taxon_name=Hydnocarpus+sumatranus", "thumbs": ["http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/6_27_20/28Jun20/Hydnocarpus2.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/6_27_20/28Jun20/Hydnocarpus4.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/6_27_20/28Jun20/Hydnocarpus1.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/6_27_20/28Jun20/Hydnocarpus6.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/6_27_20/28Jun20/Hydnocarpus7.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/6_27_20/28Jun20/Hydnocarpus5.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/6_27_20/28Jun20/Hydnocarpus3.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/pelserpb/pelserpb_25_05_16_3/IMG_20250511_071529.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/pelserpb/pelserpb_25_05_16_3/IMG_20250511_072149.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/pelserpb/pelserpb_25_05_16_3/IMG_20250511_071643.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/pelserpb/pelserpb_25_05_16_3/IMG_20250511_0722022.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/pelserpb/pelserpb_25_05_16_3/IMG_20250511_071757.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.ed